The paper focuses on evaluating the impact of different data layouts on the computational efficiency of a GPU-accelerated algorithm for interpolation. This involves aspects of computer graphics (cs.GR) and numerical analysis (cs.NA), as well as data management and storage (cs.DB) and parallel computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the application of the algorithm to practical scenarios such as environmental modeling and geostatistics suggests a potential connection to computational engineering (cs.CE).
